Everything's fine.
He just, um...

1:08:30.248 --> 1:08:32.545
He wants to spend some time
with you. That's all.

1:08:32.580 --> 1:08:35.284
He said that the two of you
would launch your rocket.

1:08:35.319 --> 1:08:38.012
-Oh, yeah, I got to finish it.
-Mm.

1:08:42.755 --> 1:08:44.590
Ma?

1:08:47.430 --> 1:08:50.431
Uh, I had a pretty good day
at school.

1:08:51.764 --> 1:08:53.533
Good.

1:09:02.610 --> 1:09:06.447
All my hopes are with you
and your brother now.

1:09:07.714 --> 1:09:10.781
You're my angels,
and you're everything to me.

1:09:14.116 --> 1:09:16.050
You're my whole life.

1:09:19.055 --> 1:09:21.594
But we're all still here.

1:09:30.198 --> 1:09:34.167
I'm not feeling so hot, buster.
I'm gonna go upstairs.

1:09:34.202 --> 1:09:35.938
(sighs)

1:09:35.973 --> 1:09:37.742
Be careful.
Your father saw a Black boy

1:09:37.777 --> 1:09:39.579
sneaking around the alleyway,

1:09:39.614 --> 1:09:42.043
so make sure you lock
everything up.

1:09:42.078 --> 1:09:43.880
-Okay.
-Okay.

1:09:55.300 --> 1:09:56.992
(whispers):
Johnny?

1:10:01.669 --> 1:10:03.801
Johnny, you there?

1:10:23.460 --> 1:10:25.292
Grandpa.

1:10:28.366 --> 1:10:30.223
GRANDPA:
<i> It's a little windy today,</i>

1:10:30.258 --> 1:10:31.895
<i> so, uh, that might affect it.</i>

1:10:31.930 --> 1:10:34.337
If we're lucky,
it'll go straight up

1:10:34.372 --> 1:10:36.768
and come straight down near us.

1:10:37.837 --> 1:10:40.343
I put these markings
on the side of the rocket.

1:10:40.378 --> 1:10:41.740
Yeah, I saw that.

1:10:41.775 --> 1:10:43.742
"USA," and you got
the old payload markings.

1:10:43.777 --> 1:10:45.238
-Yeah.
-Nice.

1:10:45.273 --> 1:10:47.911
You got a lot more patience
than I have, jelly bean.

1:10:47.946 --> 1:10:50.078
-Great job.
-Thanks, Grandpa.

1:10:50.113 --> 1:10:52.454
Okay. What happens next?
You want that?

1:10:52.489 --> 1:10:54.555
Yeah, I'm gonna need that.

1:10:55.492 --> 1:10:56.854
Listen, I just wanted
to talk to you

1:10:56.889 --> 1:10:58.526
about something, and, uh...

1:10:58.561 --> 1:11:00.693
There's something
I wanted to tell you.

1:11:00.728 --> 1:11:03.190
I'm gonna have to go away
for a few days.

1:11:03.225 --> 1:11:06.336
Uh, on a trip. Um...

1:11:06.371 --> 1:11:07.799
-Uh, hope...
-A trip?

1:11:07.834 --> 1:11:09.504
Yes, so hopefully not too long.

1:11:09.539 --> 1:11:11.704
It'll be, uh...
I'll be back soon.

1:11:11.739 --> 1:11:13.673
It's not too far--
just out on the island.

1:11:13.708 --> 1:11:15.444
I have to go check out
some things.

1:11:15.479 --> 1:11:18.139
And I wanted to tell you myself
so that you're not wondering

1:11:18.174 --> 1:11:21.043
where I am if, uh,
you don't see me around, okay?

1:11:21.078 --> 1:11:23.177
Okay, but you better
be back soon.

1:11:23.212 --> 1:11:24.651
I will, okay?

1:11:24.686 --> 1:11:26.554
-Now what? You gonna launch?
-Yeah.

1:11:26.589 --> 1:11:28.215
-Is there the...
-Is this what you want?

1:11:28.250 --> 1:11:29.722
Yes, I need that.

1:11:29.757 --> 1:11:31.460
-Good.
-Oh.

1:11:31.495 --> 1:11:33.220
You'll end up
a rocket scientist

1:11:33.255 --> 1:11:36.058
-instead of an artist.
-Mm.

1:11:37.094 --> 1:11:39.930
(robotically):
I shall check the connectors.

1:11:44.365 --> 1:11:45.639
So, how you doing?

1:11:45.674 --> 1:11:47.773
How are things
at the new school?

1:11:49.238 --> 1:11:50.941
Mm...

1:11:51.779 --> 1:11:54.747
Something's bugging you.
What is it?

1:11:56.883 --> 1:11:59.719
Sometimes kids say stuff.

1:11:59.754 --> 1:12:02.348
Kids say stuff. Yeah, they do.

1:12:02.383 --> 1:12:04.251
But, like, what kind of stuff?

1:12:04.286 --> 1:12:06.429
I don't know, they'll...

1:12:06.464 --> 1:12:09.762
say stuff, like,
about other kids.

1:12:09.797 --> 1:12:12.864
Come on. Come here.
I can't hear you.

1:12:12.899 --> 1:12:16.670
Well, they'll just say stuff
about other kids.

1:12:16.705 --> 1:12:18.265
Like what?

1:12:18.300 --> 1:12:22.445
Well, they'll say bad words
about the Black kids.

1:12:22.480 --> 1:12:24.810
Oh, yeah?

1:12:26.484 --> 1:12:28.616
Yeah, okay.

1:12:28.651 --> 1:12:31.047
And, uh...

1:12:31.082 --> 1:12:33.390
what do you do
when that happens?

1:12:35.152 --> 1:12:36.723
Come on, tell me.

1:12:36.758 --> 1:12:38.593
Obviously nothing, of course.

1:12:38.628 --> 1:12:40.254
"Nothing, of course." Yeah.

1:12:40.289 --> 1:12:42.630
You think that's funny?
You think that's smart?

1:12:42.665 --> 1:12:44.027
Well, I'll tell you
what I think.

1:12:44.062 --> 1:12:46.733
I think that's a crock
of old horseshit.

1:12:46.768 --> 1:12:47.965
I said a bad word.

1:12:48.000 --> 1:12:49.736
You got a problem with that?
Tough.

1:12:49.771 --> 1:12:51.804
I'm gonna tell you.
Now, you got to do something.

1:12:51.839 --> 1:12:54.136
You got to say something, okay?

1:12:54.171 --> 1:12:56.479
Do you know why?
'Cause you're on the ball.

1:12:56.514 --> 1:12:57.810
Right? Come on, man.

1:12:57.845 --> 1:12:59.548
You were raised better
than that.

1:12:59.583 --> 1:13:01.077
Jesus Christ.

1:13:01.112 --> 1:13:02.749
I'm going to tell you
something.

1:13:02.784 --> 1:13:05.653
I've learned over the years,
those bastards

1:13:05.688 --> 1:13:08.282
who say all that crap
and garbage to your face

1:13:08.317 --> 1:13:10.823
will then say the same stuff
behind your back.

1:13:10.858 --> 1:13:12.759
And they'll shove a knife
straight in your gut.

1:13:12.794 --> 1:13:14.497
And they'll smile
as they do it.

1:13:14.532 --> 1:13:15.894
Fuck 'em.

1:13:15.929 --> 1:13:18.600
Yeah, I said another bad word.

1:13:18.635 --> 1:13:20.162
You remember one thing.

1:13:20.197 --> 1:13:22.164
Next time those schmucks say
anything bad

1:13:22.199 --> 1:13:24.837
about those Black kids
or those Hispanics,

1:13:24.872 --> 1:13:27.774
you be a mensch
to those kids, okay?

1:13:27.809 --> 1:13:30.040
They never had your advantage.

1:13:30.812 --> 1:13:32.779
Give me a handshake.

1:13:32.814 --> 1:13:34.682
You're gonna be a mensch, okay?

1:13:34.717 --> 1:13:37.179
Firm handshake.
Okay, give me a hug.

1:13:38.721 --> 1:13:41.590
-PAUL: Love you.
-GRANDPA: Love you, too.

1:13:41.625 --> 1:13:44.219
Okay, let's get on
with the launch.

1:13:45.794 --> 1:13:47.530
Oh, I'm so nervous.

1:13:47.565 --> 1:13:48.762
Don't be nervous. Be bold.

1:13:48.797 --> 1:13:50.500
-Yes, bold. Okay.
-Go on.

1:13:50.535 --> 1:13:51.831
-Ready?
-Yeah.

1:13:51.866 --> 1:13:52.931
Here we go.
(imitates radio static)

1:13:52.966 --> 1:13:54.196
Roger. Ready for liftoff.

1:13:54.231 --> 1:13:55.835
(imitates radio static)
Over. Copy.

1:13:55.870 --> 1:13:57.199
(imitates radio static)

1:13:57.234 --> 1:13:59.773
Ten, nine, eight,

1:13:59.808 --> 1:14:03.513
seven, six, five, four,

1:14:03.548 --> 1:14:06.813
three, two, one.

1:14:10.016 --> 1:14:11.213
Oh!

1:14:11.248 --> 1:14:12.654
(laughs)

1:14:12.689 --> 1:14:15.382
-Hey, that's something. Yeah.
-Whoa!

1:14:15.417 --> 1:14:17.087
Whoa!

1:14:19.828 --> 1:14:22.092
♪ ♪

1:14:35.745 --> 1:14:37.943
PAUL:
Oh, man!

1:14:41.949 --> 1:14:43.916
PAUL:
Oh!

1:14:46.624 --> 1:14:48.855
(Paul breathing heavily)

1:14:52.597 --> 1:14:55.598
Paul. Paul.

1:14:55.633 --> 1:14:57.567
-(gasping breaths)
-Hey.

1:14:57.602 --> 1:14:59.030
Get dressed.

1:14:59.065 --> 1:15:00.735
You need to get up right now.

1:15:00.770 --> 1:15:02.770
-What?
-Get dressed.

1:15:02.805 --> 1:15:05.498
-Not for school.
-(groans softly)

1:15:05.533 --> 1:15:07.610
PAUL:
<i> What's going on?</i>

1:15:08.437 --> 1:15:11.372
Grandpa had surgery
this morning.

1:15:11.407 --> 1:15:13.011
For what?

1:15:13.046 --> 1:15:14.782
They said bone cancer.

1:15:14.817 --> 1:15:16.685
Mom knew like a month ago,
but Dad said

1:15:16.720 --> 1:15:19.787
they were worried
about how you'd take it.

1:15:19.822 --> 1:15:22.449
What do you mean?
I can take anything.

1:15:22.484 --> 1:15:24.220
I'm just...

1:15:24.255 --> 1:15:27.828
kind of worried about Mom,
how she'll react.

1:15:29.997 --> 1:15:32.195
She'll freak out if he dies.

1:15:32.230 --> 1:15:34.461
(Grandpa taking deep,
raspy breaths)

1:15:50.688 --> 1:15:52.952
(deep, raspy breaths continue)

1:16:29.727 --> 1:16:31.991
(deep, raspy breaths continue)

1:16:36.459 --> 1:16:39.130
IRVING: Ted, why don't you
take your brother out.

1:16:41.904 --> 1:16:44.168
-Come on.
-No, I want to stay.

1:16:45.237 --> 1:16:47.534
(whispers):
He shouldn't see him like this.

1:16:52.640 --> 1:16:54.376
I'm gonna stay.

1:17:16.235 --> 1:17:20.908
(airplane engine rumbling
in distance)

1:17:20.943 --> 1:17:23.240
(airplane passing)

1:17:30.216 --> 1:17:32.920
IRVING:
We don't need to stay too long.

1:17:32.955 --> 1:17:34.757
All right, just let
your mother alone.

1:17:34.792 --> 1:17:37.958
We can just stay here
in the car.

1:17:42.723 --> 1:17:44.932
Why are we staying in the car?

1:17:44.967 --> 1:17:46.428
Doesn't Mom want us out there?

1:17:46.463 --> 1:17:48.364
No, it's all right.
Let-let her, you know...

1:17:48.399 --> 1:17:50.531
Let her have her feelings,
and then...

1:17:50.566 --> 1:17:53.237
and then we can swing around
and go home.

1:17:55.142 --> 1:17:57.373
You know, you have schoolwork.

1:17:59.641 --> 1:18:02.246
Your grandfather, he, uh...

1:18:05.614 --> 1:18:07.647
...he was very kind to me.

1:18:11.895 --> 1:18:14.797
He respected me.
He's the only one.

1:18:14.832 --> 1:18:17.800
The rest of your mother's
family, they heard my father

1:18:17.835 --> 1:18:19.461
-was a plumber, and...
-(snaps fingers)

1:18:19.496 --> 1:18:22.101
...bang, they just
turned their nose up.

1:18:23.434 --> 1:18:25.170
Not him.

1:18:27.108 --> 1:18:29.570
He was...
he was a terrific guy.

1:18:30.573 --> 1:18:32.639
He held us all together.

1:18:40.957 --> 1:18:43.188
I guess it's all on me now.

1:18:46.193 --> 1:18:48.490
Goodbye, Aaron.

1:18:51.594 --> 1:18:53.495
Goodbye, Grandpa.

1:19:12.318 --> 1:19:14.087
IRVING:
Lock the doors.

1:19:14.122 --> 1:19:15.781
(Esther muttering)

1:19:15.816 --> 1:19:18.223
-Mom?
-Oh.

1:19:24.726 --> 1:19:26.803
(humming)

1:19:32.976 --> 1:19:37.572
"Louisiana Lightning"
Rod Guidry.

1:19:38.916 --> 1:19:41.510
JOHNNY:
Hey. How you doing?

1:19:44.812 --> 1:19:46.152
Hey.

1:19:46.187 --> 1:19:48.385
You were here before.

1:19:48.420 --> 1:19:50.893
-Right?
-Yeah, I was.

1:19:50.928 --> 1:19:54.193
Those dudes come by
my grandma's place again, so...

1:19:54.228 --> 1:19:56.899
I'm here for a little bit,
till it's cool to go back.

1:19:57.759 --> 1:20:00.067
I think they're gonna put her
in a home soon.

1:20:00.102 --> 1:20:01.728
Wow.

1:20:06.911 --> 1:20:09.142
I'm sorry I...

1:20:09.177 --> 1:20:11.738
I couldn't really talk
at school.

1:20:13.445 --> 1:20:15.214
They're really strict.

1:20:15.953 --> 1:20:18.415
Oh, I could see that for sure.

1:20:22.850 --> 1:20:24.256
Whoa.

1:20:24.291 --> 1:20:26.929
Hey, your toes, they're all
cut up and bleeding.

1:20:26.964 --> 1:20:28.590
You should get some Band-Aids.

1:20:28.625 --> 1:20:30.427
Come inside.

1:20:30.462 --> 1:20:32.528
Actually, it's getting
a lot better.

1:20:32.563 --> 1:20:36.598
But looks like you're all
set up with your stylin' suit.

1:20:36.633 --> 1:20:38.336
Looking good.

1:20:38.371 --> 1:20:42.076
It's for my grandpa's funeral.

1:20:42.111 --> 1:20:44.540
Oh, damn.

1:20:44.575 --> 1:20:46.311
That's heavy.

1:20:47.611 --> 1:20:50.117
You know, I've been thinking
about it for a while.

1:20:50.152 --> 1:20:52.383
My stepbro,
he's in Florida, right?

1:20:52.418 --> 1:20:55.089
Soon as I get the cash,
I go down there,

1:20:55.124 --> 1:20:56.585
make some money and do shit

1:20:56.620 --> 1:20:58.686
until I can sign up
with the Air Force or NASA.

1:20:58.721 --> 1:21:01.788
But they're building this thing
in Orlando called EPCOT.

1:21:01.823 --> 1:21:03.856
Here, look-it.

1:21:03.891 --> 1:21:05.858
You could draw there.

1:21:05.893 --> 1:21:08.168
Like you do in class.

1:21:09.336 --> 1:21:11.666
Make money that way.

1:21:14.440 --> 1:21:16.242
Seems kind of far.

1:21:16.277 --> 1:21:19.344
Shit, man, what are you staying
around here for?

1:21:22.580 --> 1:21:24.184
I know.

1:21:25.319 --> 1:21:27.990
Here, I'm gonna get you
a blanket.

1:21:28.025 --> 1:21:29.453
Okay.

1:21:29.488 --> 1:21:31.389
But I ain't gonna
stick around long, probably.

1:21:31.424 --> 1:21:33.490
But I'm thinking Florida soon.

1:21:33.525 --> 1:21:36.130
Okay. I'll be right back.

1:21:36.165 --> 1:21:38.198
All right.

1:21:45.702 --> 1:21:47.801
♪ ♪

1:21:53.941 --> 1:21:56.216
JOHNNY:
<i> Grandma.</i>

1:21:57.021 --> 1:21:59.285
We can't stay together.

1:21:59.320 --> 1:22:01.551
They're gonna take you away.

1:22:04.820 --> 1:22:06.853
I'm gonna make you proud.

1:22:13.136 --> 1:22:16.335
IRVING: And we already had to
schmear the school but good,

1:22:16.370 --> 1:22:18.040
just to get him in.

1:22:18.075 --> 1:22:20.042
The-the report,
it says he's-he's...

1:22:20.077 --> 1:22:22.044
he's not paying attention
in class.

1:22:22.079 --> 1:22:23.771
This was supposed to be
the answer.

1:22:23.806 --> 1:22:25.971
I mean, what the hell
are we supposed to do now?

1:22:26.006 --> 1:22:28.611
Irving, I don't want
to talk about this now.

1:22:28.646 --> 1:22:31.383
He doesn't have the same
potential that Ted does.

1:22:31.418 --> 1:22:32.945
He doesn't have it.

1:22:32.980 --> 1:22:35.387
-They assessed him as slow.
-ESTHER: Fuck them.

1:22:35.422 --> 1:22:37.158
-IRVING: There's something
wrong with him. -Fuck them.

1:22:37.193 --> 1:22:38.489
ESTHER:
Are you serious?

1:22:38.524 --> 1:22:40.227
IRVING:
He talks about being an artist.

1:22:40.262 --> 1:22:42.064
An artist.
His head is in the clouds.

1:22:42.099 --> 1:22:44.198
He's not living in reality.

1:22:44.233 --> 1:22:46.035
And this has to stop.

1:22:46.070 --> 1:22:48.235
It has to stop, Esther.

1:22:48.270 --> 1:22:49.863
-And the school...
-ESTHER: Irving.

1:22:49.898 --> 1:22:51.832
...the school will cost
your mother an arm and a leg.

1:22:51.867 --> 1:22:53.900
-Please, please... -Who knows
when she'll need more help

1:22:53.935 --> 1:22:55.704
now that she's alone,
she's on her own.

1:22:55.739 --> 1:22:58.410
We're-we're completely
dependent on her.

1:22:58.445 --> 1:23:00.577
Who's... who will
figure it out?

1:23:00.612 --> 1:23:02.414
The tuition's... I can't pay.

1:23:02.449 --> 1:23:08.387
I-I-I feel the-the goddamn
pressure in my chest.

1:23:09.621 --> 1:23:12.391
ESTHER:
What do you want me to do?

1:23:12.426 --> 1:23:14.525
With my father gone,
there isn't anyone

1:23:14.560 --> 1:23:16.857
that can reach him.

1:23:16.892 --> 1:23:19.024
(voice shaking):
Not you.

1:23:19.059 --> 1:23:21.466
N-Not anyone.

1:23:25.802 --> 1:23:27.670
MS. MOUSTAKAS (faint, echoing):
And each time we try

1:23:27.705 --> 1:23:29.705
to draw ourselves,
we are drawing

1:23:29.740 --> 1:23:34.380
not only what we think we see
but who we are inside.

1:23:34.415 --> 1:23:36.745
Our essence.

1:23:36.780 --> 1:23:38.780
(normal): If you need
any inspiration on essence,

1:23:38.815 --> 1:23:40.848
you can see the essence
of Paul Gauguin

1:23:40.883 --> 1:23:42.883
in this self-portrait.

1:23:42.918 --> 1:23:47.129
Look at the colors Paul Gauguin
uses to express himself, right?

1:23:47.164 --> 1:23:49.890
Blues, oranges, pinks.

1:23:49.925 --> 1:23:51.727
Paul?

1:23:51.762 --> 1:23:53.597
Earth to Paul.

1:23:54.336 --> 1:23:56.402
(chuckles)

1:23:56.437 --> 1:23:59.273
It's a spaceship drawn by
our very own space cadet.

1:23:59.308 --> 1:24:00.901
-(laughter)
-(sighs): Okay.

1:24:00.936 --> 1:24:05.213
Hey, this isn't the assignment,
but it is beautiful.

1:24:05.248 --> 1:24:06.973
So expressive.

1:24:07.008 --> 1:24:08.975
The colors he's using here.

1:24:09.010 --> 1:24:10.944
You're very talented.

1:24:12.618 --> 1:24:15.091
(whispers):
Now let's do the assignment.

1:24:16.017 --> 1:24:17.423
What are you gonna do with it?

1:24:17.458 --> 1:24:18.985
That's none of your beeswax,
Miss Bronfman.

1:24:19.020 --> 1:24:20.492
Uh, and like I was mentioning...

1:24:20.527 --> 1:24:22.494
-(school bell ringing)
-Um, that-- Pencils.

1:24:22.529 --> 1:24:24.430
(Esther crying)

1:24:24.465 --> 1:24:26.333
IRVING:
Stop, Esther.

1:24:26.368 --> 1:24:28.027
That's enough!

1:24:30.867 --> 1:24:32.735
GRANDPA:
<i> You want to be famous,</i>

1:24:32.770 --> 1:24:34.473
<i> you can do what you like,</i>
<i> but if you're gonna be famous,</i>

1:24:34.508 --> 1:24:36.277
<i> you got to sign</i>
<i> the drawings first.</i>

1:24:36.312 --> 1:24:38.708
<i> All the great artists</i>
<i> sign their work.</i>

1:24:39.876 --> 1:24:42.448
-(gasps)<i> -You're gonna be</i>
<i> an artist if you want to be.</i>

1:24:42.483 --> 1:24:44.153
<i> Nothing's gonna stop you.</i>

1:24:45.046 --> 1:24:48.388
-(siren wailing in distance)
-(heavy breathing)

1:24:55.496 --> 1:24:56.957
(Johnny grunts softly)

1:24:56.992 --> 1:24:59.630
-PAUL (whispers): Johnny.
-JOHNNY: What?

1:24:59.665 --> 1:25:02.798
PAUL: I think I know how
to make everything okay.

1:25:02.833 --> 1:25:05.207
My school has
a bunch of computers.

1:25:05.242 --> 1:25:07.000
Let's take one.

1:25:07.035 --> 1:25:08.540
Take what?

1:25:08.575 --> 1:25:10.872
Computer.
We can get it so easy.

1:25:10.907 --> 1:25:13.182
I know how to get in
and everything.

1:25:13.217 --> 1:25:14.876
We go through the window.

1:25:14.911 --> 1:25:16.680
They keep them open
all the time.

1:25:16.715 --> 1:25:18.880
You must be out of your mind.

1:25:18.915 --> 1:25:20.321
No, we can do it.

1:25:20.356 --> 1:25:22.488
We'll run away to Florida.

1:25:22.523 --> 1:25:24.952
Let's do it. Let's go.

1:25:24.987 --> 1:25:27.020
A computer?

1:25:27.924 --> 1:25:29.858
Yeah, we sell it.
It pays for the whole trip.

1:25:29.893 --> 1:25:32.432
You'll go to NASA,
and I can draw.

1:25:33.270 --> 1:25:35.061
You're coming with me.

1:25:36.031 --> 1:25:37.239
(scoffs)

1:25:37.274 --> 1:25:39.065
You can even see
your stepbrother soon.

1:25:39.100 --> 1:25:41.375
The school is just
three subway stops away.

1:25:41.410 --> 1:25:42.970
Come on.

1:25:43.005 --> 1:25:45.005
Nobody will ever know.

1:25:49.044 --> 1:25:51.110
(shuddering breaths)

1:25:53.554 --> 1:25:55.950
(Paul muttering quietly)

1:26:00.121 --> 1:26:02.088
I told you, we can't get in.

1:26:02.123 --> 1:26:03.793
PAUL:
Wait.

1:26:08.228 --> 1:26:10.239
There's no point.

1:26:10.274 --> 1:26:11.834
PAUL:
Ah, shit.

1:26:11.869 --> 1:26:13.803
JOHNNY (whispers):
There's no point.

1:26:15.642 --> 1:26:18.137
I told you. I told you.
I told you.

1:26:39.435 --> 1:26:42.062
(taking slow, deep breaths)

1:26:54.010 --> 1:26:56.010
(breath trembling)

1:26:59.279 --> 1:27:01.521
(door creaking)

1:27:17.132 --> 1:27:19.902
CROWD (echoing):
<i> Paul! Paul! Paul! Paul!</i>

1:27:19.937 --> 1:27:23.444
<i> Paul! Paul! Paul! Paul! Paul!</i>

1:27:23.479 --> 1:27:26.073
<i> Paul! Paul! Paul! Paul!</i>

1:27:26.108 --> 1:27:29.615
<i> -(chant fades)</i>
<i> -(rocket engine whooshes)</i>

1:27:30.948 --> 1:27:33.982
JOHNNY (whispers):
Dude. What are you doing?

1:27:35.051 --> 1:27:37.425
-I'm...
-What are you doing out here?

1:27:37.460 --> 1:27:39.559
This is dangerous.

1:27:40.562 --> 1:27:42.793
-Okay. -Are you sure this is
all that we need?

1:27:42.828 --> 1:27:45.158
Yeah, I-I think so.

1:27:45.193 --> 1:27:46.830
Okay. Let's go.

1:27:47.668 --> 1:27:49.800
-Okay. Okay.
-Come on, let's go.

1:27:49.835 --> 1:27:52.000
Just go. Just go. Just go.

1:27:52.035 --> 1:27:54.607
♪ ♪

1:27:54.642 --> 1:27:57.643
(siren wailing in distance)

1:27:57.678 --> 1:27:59.909
(both panting)

1:28:02.045 --> 1:28:03.880
(whispers):
I can't believe this.

1:28:04.751 --> 1:28:07.686
(whispers):
What-what do we do with it now?

1:28:08.524 --> 1:28:09.985
I got a guy.

1:28:10.020 --> 1:28:12.394
And he's got a pawnshop
on Sutphin Boulevard.

1:28:12.429 --> 1:28:14.891
And I bet he's gonna want this.

1:28:15.762 --> 1:28:17.861
So, I could take it
to him tomorrow.

1:28:17.896 --> 1:28:20.226
And then it's Florida, my man.
(laughs)

1:28:20.261 --> 1:28:23.570
That's excellent.
Okay, so we'll take a car,

1:28:23.605 --> 1:28:26.672
a bus or a-a train.

1:28:26.707 --> 1:28:27.904
I don't know. Uh...

1:28:27.939 --> 1:28:30.170
-Uh, bus could be good.
-A bus.

1:28:30.205 --> 1:28:33.239
-All right, man. Yes.
-(squeals excitedly)

1:28:33.274 --> 1:28:34.680
(Johnny sighs)

1:28:34.715 --> 1:28:36.341
(whoops) Yeah. (chuckles)

1:28:36.376 --> 1:28:37.716
PAUL:
Yes!

1:28:37.751 --> 1:28:39.982
-JOHNNY:<i> We did it!</i>
<i> -(Paul whoops)</i>

1:28:40.017 --> 1:28:41.753
TOPPER:
<i> It's my lowest grade.</i>

1:28:41.788 --> 1:28:44.393
I had, like, straight A's,
and now I have a B.

1:28:44.428 --> 1:28:45.757
It's not gonna be good.

1:28:45.792 --> 1:28:47.253
PAUL: Do your parents care
about grades?

1:28:47.288 --> 1:28:49.761
TOPPER:
Yes. So do I.

1:28:49.796 --> 1:28:52.093
GEORGE: Hey, Graff.
Did you study for the test?

1:28:52.128 --> 1:28:53.325
PAUL:
No.

1:28:53.360 --> 1:28:55.162
Oh, my God, it's like
a third of your grade.

1:28:55.197 --> 1:28:56.900
TOPPER: Dude, he's probably
just too busy

1:28:56.935 --> 1:28:59.298
drawing pictures of his hand
over and over again.

1:29:00.642 --> 1:29:02.510
I'm cutting out of here
real soon.

1:29:02.545 --> 1:29:04.006
What's that supposed to mean?

1:29:04.041 --> 1:29:07.108
-You'll see.
-Ooh, Graff's making a move.

1:29:07.143 --> 1:29:09.715
("Armagideon Time" by The Clash
playing)

1:29:09.750 --> 1:29:12.278
♪ Oh! ♪

1:29:20.827 --> 1:29:24.796
♪ A lot of people won't get
no supper tonight ♪

1:29:26.503 --> 1:29:30.538
♪ A lot of people won't get
no justice tonight ♪

1:29:30.573 --> 1:29:32.100
Dumb suitcase.

1:29:32.135 --> 1:29:36.577
♪ The battle
is getting hotter ♪

1:29:36.612 --> 1:29:39.448
♪ In this iration ♪

1:29:39.483 --> 1:29:43.617
♪ Armagideon time ♪

1:29:43.652 --> 1:29:46.015
IRVING:
Hello? Hello?

1:29:49.416 --> 1:29:51.460
(whistling a tune)

1:29:52.529 --> 1:29:54.826
-(hums softly)
-(rummaging)

1:29:56.456 --> 1:29:57.994
Who's that there?

1:29:59.360 --> 1:30:01.228
It's just me.

1:30:01.263 --> 1:30:03.802
Gonna go around back
to the clubhouse for a bit.

1:30:03.837 --> 1:30:05.331
All right,
then put out the cans.

1:30:05.366 --> 1:30:07.003
They're coming tomorrow.

1:30:07.038 --> 1:30:09.401
And, uh, your mother's sitting
shiva for your grandfather,

1:30:09.436 --> 1:30:11.645
so we'll be eating late.

1:30:11.680 --> 1:30:13.207
Okay.

1:30:15.948 --> 1:30:18.278
MAN:
<i> Stand by for mode 1 Charlie.</i>

1:30:18.313 --> 1:30:20.654
MAN 2:
<i> Stand by for mode 1 Charlie.</i>

1:30:20.689 --> 1:30:22.183
-Mark.
-Mark.

1:30:22.218 --> 1:30:23.448
Mode 1 Charlie.

1:30:23.483 --> 1:30:24.757
(indistinct radio chatter)

1:30:24.792 --> 1:30:27.188
PAUL:
Hey, Johnny.

1:30:27.223 --> 1:30:29.025
Johnny, I'm ready.

1:30:29.060 --> 1:30:33.425
♪ Remember to kick it over ♪

1:30:33.460 --> 1:30:36.362
♪ No one will guide you... ♪

1:30:36.397 --> 1:30:38.870
Okay. I'm going inside,
get the cash,

1:30:38.905 --> 1:30:41.466
and then I'll go around to
the other side of the street.

1:30:41.501 --> 1:30:42.709
Johnny.

1:30:42.744 --> 1:30:44.810
I can come with you.

1:30:44.845 --> 1:30:46.548
No, man. He trusts me.

1:30:46.583 --> 1:30:48.209
So you go and wait
till I come out.

1:30:48.244 --> 1:30:51.146
All right, all right.
I'll wait here.

1:30:51.181 --> 1:30:52.884
We're close. We're close, man.

1:30:52.919 --> 1:30:55.381
It's gonna work out.

1:30:55.416 --> 1:30:57.658
Coast is clear. Go, go.

1:30:57.693 --> 1:30:59.385
♪ A lot of people ♪

1:31:00.993 --> 1:31:03.664
♪ Use a calculator ♪

1:31:03.699 --> 1:31:06.535
♪ A lot of people
won't get no ♪

1:31:06.570 --> 1:31:08.768
♪ Supper tonight ♪

1:31:09.738 --> 1:31:12.838
♪ A lot of people
sitting down ♪

1:31:12.873 --> 1:31:14.972
♪ By the light, light, light ♪

1:31:15.007 --> 1:31:19.779
♪ The battle
is getting hotter ♪

1:31:20.749 --> 1:31:23.409
♪ Iration ♪

1:31:23.444 --> 1:31:26.412
♪ Armagideon time. ♪

1:31:32.288 --> 1:31:34.288
(song fades)

1:31:41.363 --> 1:31:43.770
WOMAN:
<i> I'm swimming with the dolphins</i>

1:31:43.805 --> 1:31:45.937
<i> here at one of Florida's</i>
<i> spectacular resorts.</i>

1:31:45.972 --> 1:31:48.808
<i> (upbeat jingle plays)</i>

1:31:57.654 --> 1:31:59.918
<i> (jingle fades)</i>

1:32:03.924 --> 1:32:06.320
(Paul's breath
trembling softly)

1:32:10.293 --> 1:32:12.329
♪ ♪

1:32:15.397 --> 1:32:17.166
(siren whoops)

1:32:25.748 --> 1:32:27.473
JOHNNY:
I didn't do anything.

1:32:27.508 --> 1:32:30.179
(indistinct chatter)

1:32:33.514 --> 1:32:35.624
(trembling breaths)

1:32:37.826 --> 1:32:40.024
(indistinct police radio
chatter)

1:32:44.525 --> 1:32:46.063
OFFICER:
Right inside here.

1:32:46.098 --> 1:32:48.032
JOHNNY:
I didn't do anything.

1:32:48.804 --> 1:32:50.870
Any weapons?

1:32:55.943 --> 1:32:58.537
10-28 requesting backup...
(continues indistinctly)

1:33:01.718 --> 1:33:04.015
(panting)

1:33:05.315 --> 1:33:07.381
(sirens wailing)

1:33:19.065 --> 1:33:21.329
(train clanking and screeching)

1:33:22.563 --> 1:33:24.497
(dog barking)

1:33:25.566 --> 1:33:26.972
(engine revving)

1:33:27.007 --> 1:33:28.842
(tires squeal)

1:33:28.877 --> 1:33:30.569
(siren whoops)

1:33:37.248 --> 1:33:39.545
(distant, indistinct chatter)

1:33:47.093 --> 1:33:49.060
We just wrapped up a 52
around the corner.

1:33:49.095 --> 1:33:50.556
Pawnshop owner called it in.

1:33:50.591 --> 1:33:52.459
It's... bad serial number
on the unit, I think.

1:33:52.494 --> 1:33:54.230
Black kid had
the computer on him.

1:33:54.265 --> 1:33:56.298
There's no contact info
for him.

1:33:56.333 --> 1:33:58.003
Could be homeless.
We don't know yet.

1:33:58.038 --> 1:34:00.170
(door bangs shut)

1:34:07.509 --> 1:34:09.575
You know this young man?

1:34:11.447 --> 1:34:12.677
Who is he?

1:34:12.712 --> 1:34:14.217
My friend.

1:34:14.252 --> 1:34:16.087
Your friend's in big trouble.

1:34:16.122 --> 1:34:18.419
He stole a computer.

1:34:19.389 --> 1:34:22.291
You want to tell me about it?

1:34:24.460 --> 1:34:26.702
I don't really know
what happened.

1:34:27.562 --> 1:34:30.134
SERGEANT:
Then what were you doing there?

1:34:32.138 --> 1:34:34.875
Huh? What are you,
a little angel?

1:34:34.910 --> 1:34:36.778
Your friend did it all?

1:34:36.813 --> 1:34:39.011
Hey!

1:34:39.046 --> 1:34:40.848
Your friend did it all?

1:34:40.883 --> 1:34:42.278
I... It...

1:34:42.313 --> 1:34:44.247
(sergeant mock stammering)

1:34:44.282 --> 1:34:46.546
No words all of a sudden,
you big shot?

1:34:46.581 --> 1:34:50.220
You want to tell me about it,
or do I have to guess?

1:34:56.723 --> 1:34:58.558
We both did it.

1:34:59.330 --> 1:35:01.594
From where I go to school.

1:35:02.839 --> 1:35:04.773
I made him come with me.

1:35:05.908 --> 1:35:08.238
It was my idea.

1:35:17.953 --> 1:35:20.481
(takes deep breath)

1:35:21.451 --> 1:35:24.122
If there's something
going on at home,

1:35:24.157 --> 1:35:26.894
if there's a family problem,
Paul,

1:35:26.929 --> 1:35:29.028
we can help you with that.

1:35:30.790 --> 1:35:32.493
Okay?

1:35:32.528 --> 1:35:34.297
We can help.

1:35:34.332 --> 1:35:37.036
You hear what
I'm saying to you?

1:35:39.876 --> 1:35:41.810
He didn't do anything.

1:35:45.849 --> 1:35:47.673
He wasn't even in there.

1:35:47.708 --> 1:35:49.851
SERGEANT:
Oh, now you want to talk to me.

1:35:49.886 --> 1:35:51.281
-(door opens)
-I don't...

1:35:52.185 --> 1:35:54.383
(indistinct whispering)

1:35:56.651 --> 1:35:59.795
We're gonna sort these little
fairy tales out later.

1:36:01.029 --> 1:36:02.831
Okay?

1:36:05.132 --> 1:36:06.692
(door opens)

1:36:06.727 --> 1:36:08.628
Why are you saying that?

1:36:09.400 --> 1:36:11.136
SERGEANT:
Keep an eye on 'em.

1:36:11.171 --> 1:36:13.237
(door closes)

1:36:14.405 --> 1:36:16.537
SERGEANT:
Mr. Graff.

1:36:18.409 --> 1:36:20.079
Yes.

1:36:21.984 --> 1:36:23.742
Irving Graff?

1:36:24.745 --> 1:36:25.854
Yes.

1:36:26.846 --> 1:36:28.285
Tom D'Arienzo.

1:36:28.320 --> 1:36:30.892
We have a mutual friend,
Nick Bloom.

1:36:30.927 --> 1:36:32.157
-Oh, yes.
-Yeah.

1:36:32.192 --> 1:36:34.159
Yes, of course. (chuckles)

1:36:34.194 --> 1:36:35.721
Tom D'Arienzo, yes.

1:36:35.756 --> 1:36:37.228
How are you?

1:36:38.066 --> 1:36:41.397
My son is...
involved in something?

1:36:42.499 --> 1:36:44.499
(sighs)

1:36:44.534 --> 1:36:47.106
Let me talk to you in here.
Come on.

1:37:07.062 --> 1:37:08.655
OFFICER:
Just sit tight.

1:37:08.690 --> 1:37:11.130
Just trying to get somebody
down here to talk to you.

1:37:11.968 --> 1:37:14.232
But we're all friends here.

1:37:14.267 --> 1:37:16.168
(chuckles):
You ain't my friend.

1:37:16.203 --> 1:37:17.829
If you're my friend,

1:37:17.864 --> 1:37:20.502
how come you guys
ain't offering me no help?

1:37:20.537 --> 1:37:24.704
It's 'cause you don't care,
and you're never gonna care.

1:37:24.739 --> 1:37:28.147
There ain't no one else gonna
stick up for me except me.

1:37:29.810 --> 1:37:32.151
OFFICER:
You get it all out?

1:37:33.220 --> 1:37:35.957
-Feel better?
-(scoffs)

1:37:35.992 --> 1:37:38.421
(footsteps approaching)

1:37:44.165 --> 1:37:46.165
Come with me.

1:37:47.432 --> 1:37:49.597
Come with me right now.

1:37:50.600 --> 1:37:53.271
SERGEANT:
Listen to your father.

1:37:55.902 --> 1:37:57.737
Let it go, man.

1:37:57.772 --> 1:38:00.476
Don't make no difference.

1:38:00.511 --> 1:38:02.577
Let it go.

1:38:04.911 --> 1:38:06.680
IRVING:
Paul.

1:38:10.752 --> 1:38:13.456
I said come on.

1:38:17.792 --> 1:38:19.858
♪ ♪

1:38:29.276 --> 1:38:31.210
Bye, Johnny.

1:38:52.299 --> 1:38:54.563
♪ ♪

1:39:03.046 --> 1:39:04.804
(engine shuts off)

1:39:11.813 --> 1:39:15.254
Please, Dad, can we just
go in the house?

1:39:17.522 --> 1:39:19.720
You don't have to hit me
this time.

1:39:20.657 --> 1:39:22.624
I won't get in trouble again.
I promise.

1:39:22.659 --> 1:39:24.923
I'm not gonna hit you, Paul.

1:39:26.432 --> 1:39:30.764
But, uh, we got very,
very lucky.

1:39:36.112 --> 1:39:39.509
I-I-I fixed that cop's
hot water heater

1:39:39.544 --> 1:39:42.446
a few years ago,
and I didn't charge him.

1:39:44.252 --> 1:39:45.812
And that's the only reason why

1:39:45.847 --> 1:39:47.682
you're not up shit's creek
right now,

1:39:47.717 --> 1:39:50.784
sitting in a juvenile
detention center somewhere.

1:39:54.427 --> 1:39:56.790
What's gonna happen
to my friend?

1:39:58.530 --> 1:40:00.959
My guess is
you never see him again.

1:40:05.141 --> 1:40:07.372
It wasn't his fault.

1:40:08.804 --> 1:40:12.113
He wasn't the one
that came up with the idea.

1:40:12.148 --> 1:40:15.314
Shut your mouth.
Shut your mouth.

1:40:16.284 --> 1:40:18.482
Listen to me.

1:40:19.650 --> 1:40:23.949
It's unfair that your friend
is gonna take the blame.

1:40:25.623 --> 1:40:29.988
All right? It's unfair,
and-and I know it hurts you.

1:40:32.135 --> 1:40:34.465
But life is unfair.

1:40:35.600 --> 1:40:39.800
Sometimes,
some people get a raw deal.

1:40:39.835 --> 1:40:41.571
And I hate that.

1:40:43.575 --> 1:40:46.675
It's-it's-it's the worst thing
in the world. It's...

1:40:48.184 --> 1:40:50.778
But you have to survive.

1:40:52.012 --> 1:40:54.980
So...

1:40:55.015 --> 1:40:56.784
...all you can do now is-is

1:40:56.819 --> 1:41:01.019
you make the most of your break
and do not look back.

1:41:03.661 --> 1:41:06.926
I don't know,
maybe I've not done a good job.

1:41:06.961 --> 1:41:08.598
I'm not your grandfather.

1:41:08.633 --> 1:41:10.831
I don't know...
I don't know how to...

1:41:14.474 --> 1:41:17.475
But I-I-I learned
a long time ago

1:41:17.510 --> 1:41:19.708
you got to be thankful...

1:41:21.481 --> 1:41:23.349
...when you're given a leg up.

1:41:23.384 --> 1:41:25.615
♪ ♪

1:41:27.487 --> 1:41:31.654
(sighs) All right,
let's-let's... let's go inside.

1:41:31.689 --> 1:41:33.986
I don't want to hear
another word about this.

1:41:34.021 --> 1:41:37.198
And your mother doesn't need
to know anything about it.

1:41:37.233 --> 1:41:40.201
She's already having
a rough enough time lately.

1:41:40.236 --> 1:41:42.027
All right?

1:41:43.239 --> 1:41:45.503
♪ ♪

